        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 3:27PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 327 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southeast of Mesita, or 15 miles southeast of Laguna Pueblo,
moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Western Albuquerque, Mesita, South Valley and Tohajiilee.

This includes Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 121 and 149.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
